873,000\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Cuba}} [[Coffee production in Cuba|Cuba]]\n| 100,000\n| 6,000\n| 13,227,000\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Panama}} [[Coffee production in Panama|Panama]]\n| 100,000\n| 6,000\n| 13,227,000\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Bolivia}} [[Coffee production in Bolivia|Bolivia]]\n| 90,000\n| 5,400\n| 11,904,000\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Timor Leste}} [[East Timor|Timor Leste]]\n| 80,000\n| 4,800\n| 10,582,000\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Central African Republic}} [[Central African Republic]]\n| 65,000\n| 3,900\n| 8,598,000\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Nigeria}} [[Nigeria]]\n| 40,000\n| 2,400\n| 5,291,000\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Ghana}} [[Ghana]]\n| 37,000\n| 2,220\n| 4,894,000\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Sierra Leone}} [[Sierra Leone]]\n| 36,000\n| 2,160\n| 4,761,000\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Angola}} [[Coffee production in Angola|Angola]]\n| 35,000\n| 2,100\n| 4,629,000\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Jamaica}} [[Coffee production in Jamaica|Jamaica]]\n| 21,000\n| 1,260\n| 2,777,000\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Paraguay}} [[Coffee production in Paraguay|Paraguay]]\n| 20,000\n| 1,200\n| 2,645,000\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Malawi}} [[Malawi]]\n| 16,000\n| 960\n| 2,116,000\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Trinidad and Tobago}} [[Trinidad and Tobago]]\n| 12,000\n| 720\n| 1,587,000\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Zimbabwe}} [[Zimbabwe]]\n| 10,000\n| 600\n| 1,322,000\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Liberia}} [[Liberia]]\n| 6,000\n| 360\n| 793,000\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Zambia}} [[Zambia]]\n| 2,000\n| 120\n| 264,000\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Coffee wars]]\n*[[List of coffeehouse chains]]\n*[[Coffee production in Colombia]]\n*[[Coffee production in Brazil]]\n*[[Coffee production in Ethiopia]]\n*[[Coffee production in Guatemala]]\n*[[Coffee production in Kenya]]\n*[[Coffee production in Hawaii]]\n*[[Coffee production in Mexico]]\n*[[Coffee production in the Philippines]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Coffee}}\n{{Coffee production}}\n{{Agriculture country lists}}\n\n[[Category:Coffee production by country| ]]\n[[Category:Lists of countries by production|Coffee]]\n", "name_user": "DonSpencer1", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "